HEADWORD: Cavy
<hw>Ca"vy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cavies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. <ets>cavia</ets>, fr.
Brazilian <ets>cabiai</ets>: cf. F. <ets>cabiai</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A rodent of the genera <gen>Cavia</gen> and
<gen>Dolichotis</gen>, as the guinea pig (<spn>Cavia cobaya</spn>).
Cavies are natives of South America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Water cavy</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>The
